<NOTE>Eds: Note contents</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An underground performer who allegedly bites the heads off two mice in the cult film `` <LOCATION> Mondo </LOCATION> <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>'' has been arrested on animal cruelty charges, an <ORGANIZATION> ASPCA </ORGANIZATION> spokesman said. <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON>, 32, a <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION> performance artist, was taken into custody by <ORGANIZATION> ASPCA </ORGANIZATION> agents at his <LOCATION> Greenwich </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Village </LOCATION> apartment Friday, said <PERSON> Jeffrey </PERSON> <PERSON> Hon </PERSON>, spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Society </ORGANIZATION> for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals. <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON> was booked at a police station on charges under the state Agriculture and Markets Law; if convicted, he could face up to one year in prison and a $ 1,000 fine per mouse, <PERSON> Hon </PERSON> said. `` While this one act may seem fairly insignificant, the whole issue of animals in entertainment is not,'' said <PERSON> Hon </PERSON>. `` We're letting people from underground acts to <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION> producers know they ca n't get away with animal cruelty. <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON> was still being processed by police and could not immediately be reached for comment. `` <LOCATION> Mondo </LOCATION> <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>,'' a cult favorite which plays in weekend midnight shows at a <LOCATION> Greenwich </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Village </LOCATION> theater, features an assortment of bizarre acts from the downtown <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION> scene. Although the film was released earlier this summer, <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON> was not arrested because <ORGANIZATION> ASPCA </ORGANIZATION> investigators hoped to catch him in the act during one of his live performances, <PERSON> Hon </PERSON> said. Authorities have an eyewitness to <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON>'s performance and decided to arrest him after receiving a tip that he was leaving for <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>, he said. In his scene, <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON> allegedly bites the heads off two mice and spits them into the audience. According to <PERSON> Hon </PERSON>, the scene has outraged animal rights activists, including television game show host <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Barker </PERSON>. `` <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Barker </PERSON> has been very keen for us to arrest this guy <PERSON> Coleman </PERSON> so legislators can see exactly what's going on,'' said <PERSON> Hon </PERSON>.
