 Comedian <PERSON> Joan </PERSON> <PERSON> Rivers </PERSON> is currently in negotation with with <ORGANIZATION> Tribune </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Entertainment </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> about hosting a daytime television talk show, according to industry newspaper reports. The former host of <ORGANIZATION> Fox </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s `` The Late Show'' and guest host of <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` The Tonight Show Starring <PERSON> Johnny </PERSON> <PERSON> Carson </PERSON>'' is said to be working out a deal for a 26-week cycle beginning in the fall of 1989 that would serve as a counterpart to <ORGANIZATION> Tribune </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Geraldo. Neither Miss Rivers nor <ORGANIZATION> Tribune </ORGANIZATION> could be reached for comment in calls made after business hours. Although a contract has not been signed, it was only a matter of `` crossing the T's and dotting the I's,'' according to Friday's editions of The Hollywood Reporter The talk show would be carried by the six Tribune-owned television stations, including <ORGANIZATION> KTLA </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> WPIX </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> and WGN in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>, The <ORGANIZATION> Daily </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Variety </ORGANIZATION> reported in its Friday editions. Miss Rivers is currently appearing on <LOCATION> Broadway </LOCATION> in <PERSON> Neil </PERSON> <PERSON> Simon </PERSON>'s `` Broadway Bound. She also stars as the permanent `` center square'' on television's `` Hollywood Squares.'' Miss Rivers vacated the guest host spot on the <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> talk show in 1986 to take the starring role in `` The Late Show,'' which debuted Oct. 9, 1986. The show got lower ratings than expected, and she left the program in May 1987.
