ncluded. <PERSON> Burnett </PERSON> also rejected <PERSON> Rowan </PERSON>'s claim of exemption from the gun control law on the grounds that he uses his home as a business, not just a residence. <PERSON> Benjamin </PERSON> <PERSON> N. </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON>, 19, of suburban <LOCATION> Chevy </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Chase </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Md. </LOCATION>, was wounded in the wrist when <PERSON> Rowan </PERSON> caught him and three others taking a swim in his backyard pool. <PERSON> Rowan </PERSON> says he shot <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> when the teen-ager lunged at him, but <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> said he was shot while trying to flee.
