<DATELINE>MATAMOROS, Mexico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Hurricane <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON> powered into <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>'s eastern coast Friday for the second time in three days, forcing thousands of residents from their homes after killing at least 21 people on the <LOCATION> Yucatan </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Peninsula </LOCATION> Heavy rains from the storm also drowned eight people in <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION>, where officials said about 6,000 people were homeless and 27,000 acres of crops were destroyed. The eye of the hurricane crossed onto land at 5:35 p.m. EDT -LRB- 4:35 p.m. CDT -RRB-, sweeping ashore 120 miles south of <LOCATION> Brownsville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hurricane </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Coral </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gables </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, said in a statement. <LOCATION> Brownsville </LOCATION> is just across the <LOCATION> Rio </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Grande </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> Matamoros </LOCATION>, a city of 280,000 people. <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON> _ a 450-mile-wide hurricane with winds of 120 mph _ made landfall just north of <LOCATION> La </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pesca </LOCATION>, a fishing village on the <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>. The coastal plain in that zone is sparsely populated. The confirmed <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> death toll rose to 21, <PERSON> Jorge </PERSON> <PERSON> Galicia </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Civil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> System </ORGANIZATION> told <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> early Saturday. All occurred in the three <LOCATION> Yucatan </LOCATION> <LOCATION> peninsula </LOCATION> states of <LOCATION> Campeche </LOCATION>, Yucatan and <PERSON> Quintana </PERSON> <PERSON> 