<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> sent a `` special message to the people of <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>'' Saturday, assuring them the federal government is ready to help clean up the damage caused by Hurricane <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON>. `` Today, as you wait for the waters to recede and the cleanup to begin, <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> and I and all Americans hold you in our prayers,'' he said in his weekly radio address, delivered from the presidential retreat at Camp David. `` We all have one blessing to count. Warning came early. You were ready. So were we,'' he said. `` The federal government has spent the last week preparing to help during and after the storm,'' <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> said. `` We have offered help also to our international friends who felt <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON>'s full fource. As I told Jamaican Prime Minister <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Seaga </PERSON>, we are ready to play an active role in helping them rebuild.''
