<HEAD>Construction Site Turns To Fish Grab, And Grabbers Get Ticketed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALEXANDRIA, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A highway construction site turned into a fish grab when part of a bayou was drained, leaving a wide, muddy hole where men with nets, buckets and spears sloshed around after fish. But not for long: state wildlife and fisheries agents armed with ticket books quickly put the brakes on the landlubber fishermen Friday. `` The people who got citations were the ones in the water actively chasing the fish,'' said Capt. <PERSON> Burton </PERSON> <PERSON> Wiley </PERSON> of the wildlife department. `` We did n't write up anyone who was picking up dead fish off the bank. If they want to scavenge, that's their business.'' Agents ticketed only people who caught gamefish such as bass or perch from the water, letting them keep trash fish such as catfish, gar and buffalo fish, he said. But men at the construction scene after the incident disputed <PERSON> Wiley </PERSON>, saying the game wardens confiscated all of the fish, including catfish and buffalo fish. And, they said, nobody was allowed to pick up any of the fish at the site. `` I do n't think it is right for us to have to pay a big fine for catching fish that were going to die anyway,'' the <ORGANIZATION> Alexandria </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Daily </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Town </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Talk </ORGANIZATION> quoted an unidentified participant as saying. The minimum penalty for violating state gamefish regulations is $ 25. <PERSON> Wiley </PERSON> said the best thing for the contractor to have done with unharmed fish stranded in the pool have been to dump them into the bayou on the other side of the earthen dam. Project engineer <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON> <PERSON> Boniol </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> and Development said he was not present when the tickets were issued and is not familiar with state laws governing taking fish at a construciton site. `` That's not in the plans and specifications we drew up for this project,'' he joked.
