</PERSON> <PERSON> Jordan </PERSON>, which produces tampers at a plant in <LOCATION> Ludington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mich. </LOCATION>, ranks third in <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> production behind <ORGANIZATION> Plasser </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Theurer of <LOCATION> Austria </LOCATION>, which operates a plant in <LOCATION> Chesapeake </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>. A receptionists answering the telephone at <LOCATION> Jackson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION> headquarters said the company's offices were closed for the weekend and that officials could not be reached for comment Calls to <ORGANIZATION> Ivaco </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Montreal </LOCATION> were unanswered.
